<title>Nemzet 1996.05.14</title><BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000"><h1>Nemzet 1996.05.14</h1><!-- body="start" --><pre>Subject: Nemzet 1996.05.14X-Subscribe__: <A HREF = "mailto:subs.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com">subs.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com</A>X-Unsubscribe: <A HREF = "mailto:unsubs.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com">unsubs.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com</A>X-WWW_Page___: http://www.siliconvalley.com/nemzet.htmlX-Disclaimer_: Dissemination of information is for public benefit,X-Disclaimer_: responsibility for content is not assumed.N     N  EEEEEEE  M     M  ZZZZZZZ  EEEEEEE  TTTTTTTNN    N  E        MM   MM       Z   E           TN N   N  E        M M M M      Z    E           TN  N  N  EEEE     M  M  M     Z     EEEE        TN   N N  E        M     M    Z      E           TN    NN  E        M     M   Z       E           TN     N  EEEEEEE  M     M  ZZZZZZZ  EEEEEEE     T--->> M A G Y A R   I N T E R N E T   V I L A G L A P <<---Vitacikk, Level Szerkesztosegnek:Alairassal: <A HREF = "mailto:signed.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com">signed.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com</A>Alairas nelkul: <A HREF = "mailto:noname.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com">noname.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com</A>Szerkesztosegnek: <A HREF = "mailto:editor.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com">editor.nemzet@magyar.siliconvalley.com</A>=HAZAI SAJTOSajtokivonatok napi- es hetilapokbol [Szent Hirek, a Sorok KoztOlvaso szabad velemenyeivel tarkitva] UM: Uj M.o., MN: MagyarNemzet, NSZ: Nepszabadsag, MH: Magyar Hirlap, NSZV: Nepszava,EH: Esti Hirlap, HVG: Heti Vilaggazdasag, VG:Vilaggazdasag,NG: Napi Gazdasag. A magyar copyright egyszer mar megjelentnapi- es hetilap anyagot szabadon utankozolhetonek tart.1. Kulfold[Nem csak az USA, de M.o. is megsertette a boszniai embargot]Meg nem nevezett bosnyak kormanytisztviselok szerint a tobbi kozottMagyarorszagon at is erkezett penz es hadfelszereles a boszniaihadsereg felfegyverzesere 1993-tol. A Washington Post ezt egy kulugyiszovivore hivatkozva allitja. Magyar illetekesek minden alapotnelkulozonek tartjak a fenti vadat. A HM illetekesei szerint viszontnem zarhato ki, hogy a szaz magyar fegyverkereskedelmi vallalkozasesetleg megsertette a tilalmat (NSZ, NSZV). [Mint ismeretes, azUSA sajtoja nyiltan elismerte, hogy az USA szabad kezet adott aboszniai embargo megsertesere, ami a magyar fegyverkereskedelmetfelbatoritotta. Mint felberelt zsebtolvajra, most hogy lebuktaka fokolomposok, M.o.-ra kenik az akcio odiumat][70% valoszinuseggel polgarhaboru lesz Oroszorszagban]Az Oroszorszagban legutobb vegzett kozvelemeny-kutatasok adataiszerint a juniusi elnokvalasztasok elott Borisz Jelcin 1,5-4szazalekkal vezet a kommunista Gennagyij Zjuganov elott. Alexandr Lebegytabornok, az egyik elnokjelolt szerint a juniusi oroszelnokvalasztasokat 70 szazalekos valoszinuseggel polgarhaborufogja kovetni. Alekszandr Vengerovszkij, a Liberalis Demokrata Part voltmasodik embere azt allitja, hogy Vlagyimir Zsirinovszkij valojaban amaffia fedoszerveve valt (NSZ, NSZV).2. Gazdasag[Csodben a tarsadalombiztositas]Medgyessy penzugyminiszter javaslatara munkacsoport jon letre, amely atb-alapok hianyanak okat es a csokkentes modjat vizsgalja.A lap ugy tudja, hogy a gazdasagi kabinet 30 milliard forint tervenfeluli kiadast allapitott meg az APV Rt.-nel.A nyugdijbiztositasi alapba az elso negyedevben az idoaranyosanelvarhato bevetelek 93 szazaleka folyt be, es egyebek kozott ennekkovetkezmenye, hogy az alap a marciust 11,4 milliard forintos hiannyalzarta, mikozben az egesz evi deficit, a koltsegvetesi torvenyertelmeben 16,25 milliard forint lehetne. A nyugdijbiztosito mairendkivuli kozgyulese, e tema mellett megvitatja a mult hetikormanyulesen elfogadott nyugdijreform-elkepzeleseket (MH).[A nyugdijhelyzet idozitett bomba]30-40 ev mulva mar 70 ev fole novekszik a nyugdijkorhatar az EUorszagaiban. Az unio brusszeli bizottsaga minden korabbinal riasztobbkepet festve idozitett bombanak nevezi a tagallamok nyugdijhelyzetet.Kokeny Mihaly, a Nepjoleti Miniszterium allamtitkara szerintMagyarorszagon nem fenyeget tovabbi korhataremeles (VG).[Egyeni vallalkozok korulrohogik az adorendszert]Az ipari es epitoipari tevekenyseget vegzo egyeni vallalkozok az1995. evre az elozo evi 53 ezer forinttal szemben 36 ezer forint evesjovedelmet vallottak be. A szellemi munkaval foglalkozo vallalkozokkimutatott jovedelme 70 ezerrol 67 ezer forintra merseklodott - mondtaa NSZ-nak Pitti Zoltan, az APEH elnoke, aki szerint az elso negyedevi adobevetelek osszessegeben a tervezettnek megfeleloen folytak be.3. Belfold[Arcatlan hazudozas Franka "Uj Magyarorszagaban"]Az Uj Magyarorszagtol tavozo nehany szerkeszto es publicistaszerint a napilap tulajdonosai felhaborito es valotlan indokokkalvaltottak le a mult heten az eddigi foszerkesztot, s olyan tartalmuvaltozasokat ohajtanak keresztulvinni, amelyek megszuntetnek a lapfuggetlenseget. Az ellenvelemenyt megfogalmazok kozlemenye tudatja:a foszerkesztovaltassal parhuzamosan Dippold Pal felelosszerkesztot, az Allaspont rovat szerkesztojet olyan feladattalkivantak megbizni, hogy a rovat politikai elet tompitsa,gyakorisagat csokkentse, es kulso szerzoket lehetoleg nefoglalkoztasson. Dippold azonban ezt nem vallalta, es onkent tavozott.Lovas Lajos es helyettese, Tallai Gabor pedig az UMA kulturalisrovatanak szerkeszteset adta vissza. Manyoki Endre, a magazinszerkesztoje, tovabba Kiss Gy. Csaba fomunkatars szinten felallt.Szokolay Sandor zeneszerzo megvalt szerkesztobizottsagi tagsagatol.A nyilatkozat alairoi - Agh Istvan, Dippold Pal, Hatar Gyozo, LovasIstvan, Kocsis L. Mihaly, Ko Andras, Pokol Bela, Toth Gy. Laszlo -kijelentik: a tortentek miatt huseguk a laphoz megszunt. Az UMAszerkesztosege cafolja a vadakat (UM). [Franka kijelentette aNSZ-ban, hogy "nem fog cenzurazni" -- ami egy arcatlanul hazugallaspont. Franka ugyanis a lap foszerkesztoje ES gazdasagi vezetoje, tehat korlatlan ur mi jelenik meg a lapban es mi nem][Az Orszaggyuloles folytatja munkajat a Parlamentben: Csodhelyzet]Az Orszaggyulesben tegnap napirend elott hosszadalmas vita bontakozottki a gazdasag allapotarol. Csepe Bela (KDNP) hangsulyozta: komolyveszelyt jelent a fizetesi merleg megnovekedett hianya, megrendult azallamhaztartas pozicioja a tb-alapoknal, ezert nem lesz tarthato aGDP negy szazalekot meg nem halado hianya. Szukseg leszpotkoltsegvetesre is. Varga Mihaly (Fidesz) szerint gazdasagiszempontbol Magyarorszag a regio utolso harmadaba kerult, lassu agazdasagi novekedes. Kadar Bela (MDF) ugy fogalmazott: nincs ugyandramai helyzet a gazdasagban, de sok a kedvezotlen jel. Ilyen, hogy amagyar vallalkozok kiszorulnak a belso piacokrol. Csokkent a lakossagmegtakaritasa, ami rossz jel a jovobe vetett bizalmat illetoen.Torgyan Jozsef (FKGP) arrol beszelt, hogy a tb rendszere az osszeomlasszelere kerult. Pusztai Erzsebet (MDNP) az egeszsegugyi dolgozokberemelesere tett es be nem valtott kormanyfoi igeretet emlegette.A kormany neveben Akar Laszlo politikai allamtitkar leszogezte: akormany kozel all eredeti programjanak teljesitesehez. BuranySandor (MSZP) arrol szolt, hogy a kormany erre az evre a kedvezotlengazdasagi folyamatok megallitasat igerte, ezt teljesitette is. Alakossag szamara a javulas csak 1998-tol lesz erzekelheto. Akepviselok lefolytattak a Budapest Banknak juttatott 12 milliardosallami tamogatas korulmenyeinek vizsgalatarol szolo hatarozatijavaslat reszletes vitajat. A kormany torvenymodosito javaslatabaninditvanyozta, hogy a nagyobb onkormanyzatokat kotelezzekkonyvvizgalo megbizasara. Az ellenzek is egyetertett az emberi jogibizottsagnak a kisebbsegi onkormanyzatok koltsegvetesitamogatasara vonatkozo javaslataval (NSZ, UM).[Koalicios valsag: mar magnofelvetellel bizonyitjak egymashazugsagait, a kisebbseg megvetozza a tobbseget]A kormanyulesrol magnofelvetel keszul, az arrol keszitendo szoszerinti jegyzokonyv feltetelezhetoen bizonyitja, hogy nem szuletettdontes a kozponti nyomozohivatal felallitasarol, a miniszterelnokcsak tajekozodo szavazast rendelt el - jelentette ki Peto Ivanfrakciovezeto az SZDSZ kepviselocsoportjanak hetfoi ulese utan. AzSZDSZ ugyvivoi testulete tegnapi ulesen felhatalmazta Kuncze Gabort,hogy amennyiben a kormany valtozatlan formajaban kivanja a parlamentele terjeszteni a nyomozohivatallal kapcsolatos eloterjesztest, akkoreljen a koalicios szerzodesben rogzitett vetojogaval - nyilatkoztaHack Peter ugyvivo. Azt is elmondta: a testulet tamogatja azt a belugyminiszteriumi csomagot, amely a meglevo szervezetrendszert erositene meg, beleertve az ugyeszseget es a birosagokat, ez hatekony fellepest tenne lehetove (NSZ).[Nagy gazdasagi bunozes nagy igazsagugyi zavarosban halaszassalparosul]A nagy gazdasagi ugyek nem jutnak el a Legfelsobb Birosag ele. GyorgyiKalman legfobb ugyesz elmondta: az ugyeszek azert a helyi es nem amegyei birosagok elott emelnek vadat a gazdasagi buntetougyekben,mert a buntetoeljarasi torveny ezt irja elo. Gyorgyi Solt Palnak,a Legfelsobb Birosag elnokenek a kormanyfohoz irt levelerereagalt, amelyben ezeknek az ugyeknek a megyei birosagok eleutalasat javasolta.(NSZ)[Oktatasugy halaltusaja] Horn Gabor, az SZDSZ orszaggyulesi kepviseloje szerint szakmailagelfogadhatatlan az a kormanydontessel utolag megerositett"kompromisszum", hogy a tanarok kotelezo oraszamanak novelesetreszben csak februarban vezetnek be. Elkepesztonek tartotta egy ilyenvaltoztatas ev kozbeni bevezeteset, ezert az SZDSZ modositoinditvanyt nyujt be a kozoktatasi torveny kormany altal elfogadottvaltozatahoz, es ragaszkodik ahhoz, hogy a novelest szeptemberbenhajtsak vegre, ha maskent nem megy, csak 1997-ben. SzollosiIstvanne, a PSZ fotitkara elmondta: reszerol semmi akadalya nincs ajovo szeptemberi oraemelesnek (NSZV, NSZ).[Kivel egyesuljon a kiskoru?]Az Alkotmanybirosag tegnap hatarozatot hozott a Legfelsobb Birosagelnokenek alkotmanyertelmezest kero inditvanyarol, mely szerintosszeutkozesbe kerul egymassal ket alapjog: a gyermek megfelelofejlodesenek allami garantalasa, illetve az ot megilletoegyesulesi jog abban az esetben, ha a kiskoru homoszexualis egyesulettagja kivan lenni. A testulet hatarozata megallapitja, hogy azallamnak kotelessege a gyermek fejlodesenek vedelme. Ez alkotmanyosalapot nyujt arra, hogy a torvenyhozo vagy a birosag a gyermekalapjogainak, ezen belul egyesulesi jogainak gyakorlasat korlatozza.Az AB ramutat arra, hogy az allamnak a gyermeket meg kell ovnia az olyankockazatvallalasoktol is, amelyeket eletkoranal fogva nem kepesertekelni. Ezert a torvenyhozo vagy a birosag kizarhatja, hogy agyermek homoszexualis egyesulet tagja lehessen. A korlatozasnak agyermek fejlodeset fenyegeto konkret kockazathoz kell igazodnia, agyermek erettsegenek es az egyesulet jellegenek merlegelese alapjan(NSZ).[Tizennegykaratos auto]Szabo Gyorgy nepjoleti miniszter a mult heti sajtobiralatokrareagalva intezkedett az uj gepkocsi-vasarlasi kiirasvisszavonasara. Alighogy kiadtak az ezzel kapcsolatos kozlemenyt,erkezett a hir, hogy elloptak a miniszter szolgalati BMW-jet. Ennekellenere sem modositja a dontest (MH).[MDF-KDNP szovetseg]Az ellenzek tengelye kivan lenni az MDF es a KDNP, ezert a jovobenszorosabbra fuzik kapcsolataikat. Ugyanakkor mindket part vezetojeszeles koru ellenzeki osszefogasban gondolkodik, mert ugy velik,hogy jelenlegi ellenfeluket, az MSZP-SZDSZ koaliciot csak igy lehetlegyozni az 1998-as valasztasokon. Tegnap delelott tobb mint negyoran keresztul targyalt zart ajtok mogott Giczy Gyorgy, a KDNP esLezsak Sandor, az MDF elnoke a Gellert Szalloban. Lezsak azeszmecseret koveto sajtotajekoztaton hangsulyozta: meggyozodese,hogy ez a megbeszeles uj fejezetet nyit a ket part eleteben. Giczyarrol szolt, hogy Lezsak partelnokke valasztasaval helyreallt abizalom az MDF es a KDNP kozott. Mindket partvezeto ugy veli, hogyaz MDNP nem politikai tenyezo. Lezsak kozolte: egyelore nem kivannakveluk targyalni, egyreszt mert a Neppart negativ kampanyt folytat azMDF ellen, masreszt egyelore nincsen vezetosege. Ugyanakkor korrektegyuttmukodesre torekszenek a Fidesszel es nyitottak az FKGP irantis. Lezsak Sandor kijelentette: az MSZP-SZDSZ kormanygazdasagpolitikaja embert megveto, a jelenlegi koalicio felszabadorszagga silanyitotta Magyarorszagot. E politika elleneben kell azellenzeknek osszefognia. Giczy is hangsulyozta: mindket part nagyonszeles koru egyuttmukodest szeretne (MN, NSZ).[Orban tovabbra is vetozni akarja a kisgazdakat]Orban Viktor szerint fuggetlenul attol, hogy a KDNP honapokkal ezelotteldontotte tavolmaradasat az ellenzeki szovetsegbol, a doktrinavaltozatlan maradt: vagy egyutt veri meg az ellenzek a kormanypartokat,vagy sehogy. A Fidesz elnoke a XIII. keruleti polgari egyuttmukodesiegyesulet meghivasara tartott beszedeben a leendo ellenzekiegyuttmukodes helyet ugy hatarozta meg, hogy az mindenkeppen azSZDSZ-tol jobbra kezdodik, es a kisgazdakig terjedo politikai terbenmozgo, mersekelt ellenzeki partokra terjed ki. Orban partja nevebenleszogezte: helyesnek talaljak a helyi es megyei onkormanyzatszintjeig az egyuttmukodest a kisgazdakkal is, efolott azonbanegyelore nem. A Fidesz ugyanakkor a bekes egymas mellettelesretorekszik az FKGP-vel, s mind fogalmazott: mindenkepp ugyelni kell arra,nehogy egy kisgazdaellenes nepfrontot alakitson ki a kormanykoalicio.Annal inkabb nem tartana ezt szerencsesnek a Fidesz elnoke, mert apart jobboldali szavazoira mindenkeppen szuksege van az ellenzeknek,raadasul minden konfliktus az FKGP-vel csak gyengitene az ellenzekvalasztasi eselyeit. Orban alahuzta: azt tartana helyesnek, ha azFKGP jeloltjei kulon indulnanak az 1998-as parlamenti valasztasokon,mig a tobbi ellenzeki part kozos jelolteket inditana. Kerdesrekozolte: sem az MDF, sem a KDNP nem szabhat olyan felteteleket, amelyek aFidesz szamara elfogadhatatlanok. Szerinte mindenkepp egy ketpolusubalkozep-jobbkozep felosztasra van szukseg, mert Magyarorszag amostani hatparti viszonyok kozott hosszu tavon kormanyozhatatlan.Oromet fejezte ki, hogy hosszu tavon egyuttmukodesre kepesbalkozep alakult ki a politikai eletben (MH, MN).[Rakosista szintu propagandakampanyra kapcsolt a liberalbolsevizmus]Mi az oka annak, hogy ma tobben gondoljak, mint az elozo ciklusfelidejeben, 1992-ben, hogy rossz iranyba mennek a dolgok, megis messzeelmarad az Antall-kormany akkori 27 szazalekos tamogatottsaga aHorn-kabinet 52 szazalekpontjatol? A NSZV-ban politikusok nyilatkoznakerrol. Szekeres Imre (MSZP) leszogezte: az, amire ma a Horn-kormanyvallalkozik, hogy atalakitsa a gazdasagot, talalkozik avalasztopolgarok akarataval, s ez az oka annak is, hogy az ellenzeklegures terbe kerult, nincs mondanivaloja. Peto Ivan (SZDSZ)velemenye: kozvelemeny-kutatasok is bizonyitjak, hogy a parlamentiellenzek nem komoly tenyezo az Orszaggyulesben. Ennek oka, hogy azellenzeki partok nem tanultak hibaikbol: ma is gyakran ideologizalnak,mikozben a magyar tarsadalomrol kiderult, a gyakorlatisagot tamogatja.Varga Mihaly (Fidesz) az irott es elektronikus mediaban tapasztalhatokormanyzati tulsullyal magyarazza, hogy nepszeruek a koaliciopartjai. Megis ugy gondolja, az ellenzeki partok esetlegesszovetsegkotesevel 1998-ban megnyerhetok a bizonytalan szavazok.Szerinte az idei ev valoszinuleg nem hoz fordulatot a jobboldali partokegyuttmukodeseben, igy a Fidesz onalloan keszul a kampanyra.Rasko Gyorgy (MDNP) szerint ahogy az MSZP lerazta az "utodpart"jelzot, ugy nekik is sikerulhet, fokent valamely partszovetsegtagjakent meggyozni a valasztokat, hogy mar nem azonosak az 1994-benmegbukottakkal. Rasko velemenye: az MDF harmadikutassaga ma marertelmezhetetlen, nepfrontos gazdasagpolitikaja folott eljart azido. Demeter Ervin (MDF) a szocialis piacgazdasagot megvalositandoegyseges ellenzeki programban latja a jobboldali partok kitoresilehetosegeit. Csepe Bela (KDNP) figyelmeztet: a kormanypartoknepszerusegnovekedese is azt mutatja, hogy ha a jobboldal a jelenlegipolitizalast folytatja, nem kepes megfelelni a varakozasoknak.Letfontossagu, hogy egyeztetesek utan egyseges ellenzeki programmalalljanak a valasztok ele. [A fenti hazugsagozon a Rakosi-Kadar korszak ota pelda nelkuli propagandakampanyt jelez] (NSZV)[Ki hazudik (nagyobbat); az MDNP vagy az SZDSZ?]A XI. keruleti polgarmestere, Szegedi Ferenc (MDNP) cafolta LakosImrenek (SZDSZ) a kepviselotestulet penzugyi bizottsaga elnokenekazt a vasarnapi nyilatkozatat, mely szerint egymilliardos hianya lettvolna tavaly a keruletnek. A penzugyi bzottsag megtargyalta az 1995.evi zarszamadast es - egyhangulag - javasolja annak elfogadasat akepviselotestuletnek. Teny, hogy a XI. keruleti onkormanyzat 1995-benmegorizte fizetokepesseget - kozolte a polgarmester, hangsulyozva,hogy az ASZ aprilisi vizsgalata sem talalt torvenysertesre utalointezkedeseket. Lakos tovabbra is fenntartja allitasat (MH).[Erzsebetvaros csodben]Az Erzsebetvarosi onkormanyzat csod szelere sodrodott. A VII.keruletnek mar a pedagogusok nyari beret sincs mibol kifizetnie. Akepviselotestulet felfuggesztette allasabol es fegyelmi inditottaz eladosodasert felelosse tett Bakonyi Karola polgarmester ellen, akicafolja a fizeteskeptelenseget, s az ellene inditott fegyelmittorvenytelennek tartja (MH).[Kielegitesek a "Magyarorszag" hetilap ugyeben]A Fovarosi Munkaugyi Birosag Molnar Erika vezette tanacsa SpeidlZoltan, a Magyarorszag cimu hetilap volt foszerkesztoje es OltvanyiTamas, a lap egykori rovatvezetoje munkaugyi pereben hetfon meghozottdontese helyt adott a felperesek keresetenek. A tanacs ugy iteltemeg, hogy az Exkluziv Kft. tavaly novemberben jogellenesen szuntette meg aket vezeto munkaviszonyat. Az itelet indoklasa szerint a felperesekmunkaviszonyat folyamatosnak kell tekinteni, ezert az alperes ExkluzivKft.-nek a felperesek reszere - vegkielegites gyanant - meg kellteritenie a 15, illetve 12 havi atlagberuknek megfelelo, valamint afelmentesuk idejere jaro osszeget. Speidl Zoltan eseteben ez azosszeg 2617500, Oltvanyi Tamas eseteben pedig 786500 forint (MH).=ALFA HANGOKAlfa hangok - mobil vonalonjalso@cric.chemres.hu (George Jalsovszky)Orszagos eletvedo szovetseg alakult        Az Alfa Szovetseg olyan polgari szervezetek kezdemenyezesere alakultmeg, amelyek egyetertenek abban, hog a tarsadalom jovojet elsesorban a magyermekeinek biztonsaga, a gyermekvedelem eredmenyessege hatarozza meg. Azuj orszagos szervezet kuzdeni kivan a magzati elet vedelmeert, meg akarjamenteni azokat a csecsemoket, amelyeket anyjuk elhagyna vagy elpusztitana.        A Szovetseg olyan alapitvanyok es szervezetek tevekenyseget hangoljaossze, amelyek segitseget nyujtanak a valsaghelyzetben levo terhes nonek escsaladjanak abban, hogy a magzat biztonsagosan megszulethessek, es verszerinti szulei szemelyeben szereto csaladot kapjon, illetve, ha a gyermeknem kivantkent jon a vilagra vagy csalad nelkul marad, hozzasegitik,. hogymielobb orokbefogado vagy nevelo csaladba keruljon.        A fenti celok megvalositasahoz a szovetseg 19, regionkentimunkatarsa egy-egy mobil telefont kapott, amelyet a hozzajuk fordulokhivhatnak, s amellyel egymas kozott ingyen beszelhetnek. Ugyancsakrendelkezesre all egy kozponti "zold szam", amely barhonnan dijmentesenhivhato. A telefonszamokon (06-30-541-000-tol 06-30-541-018-ig az egyesregiok szama, 06-80-541-019 a "zold szam") az "alfa hangok" olyan varandosnok jelentkezeset varjak, akik allapotukat nem kivant tehernek erzik, essegitseget kernek.        A jelentkezoknek igeny szerint: lelki tamaszt nyujtanak,tajekoztatjak lehetosegeikrol, a lakohelyhez legkozelebb allo egeszsegugyiszolgaltatasokrol. Szukseg eseten a megfelelo tagszervezethez iranyitjak,amely segitseget nyujt abban, hogy a szulesig tarto idoszakban kornyezeteelol elrejtozzek megfelelo egeszsegugyi ellatast is biztositokismama-otthonban, s esetleg a szulest kovetoen gyermekevel az otthonbanmaradhasson. A tagszervezet anyagilag es termeszetbeni tamogatassal issegiteni tudja ot es csaladjat, hogy kepesse valjon a szuletendo gyermekfogadasara.        Tehat ne feledjuk: 06-80-541-019 a "zold szam". INGYENES!!!=REGIONALIS HIREK ES OROSZ VALASZTASOMRI RUSSIAN PRESIDENTIAL ELECTION SURVEYCENTRAL ELECTORAL COMMISSIONZYUGANOV LUCKIEST IN DRAWING FOR TV TIME. On 5 May, the CentralElectoral Commission held a random drawing to allocate free air time onradio and television, and Communist leader Gennadii Zyuganov emerged inthe strongest position, Nezavisimaya gazeta reported. Between 14 May and4 June, each presidential candidate will receive two ten-minute slots onthe Channel 1 broadcaster Russian Public TV (ORT) and two on the Channel2 broadcaster Russian TV (RTR)--one in the morning and one in theevening. Between 5 and 14 June, each candidate will receive two five-minute slots on ORT and RTR. St. Petersburg Channel 5 will also provide30 minutes of free air time to each candidate, but all at once.President Boris Yeltsin's last free televised appearance will be on ORTon the evening of 11 June. Vladimir Zhirinovsky was more fortunate--hedrew the evening slot on ORT for 13 June. Grigorii Yavlinskii willappear for the last time on ORT on the morning of 11 June, but he willbe on RTR on the evening of 13 June. Not only will Zyuganov appear onboth ORT and RTR on the morning of 13 June, he will also receive fiveminutes of free air time on ORT and a full half hour on St. PetersburgTV on the evening of 14 June, the last day campaigning in the media ispermitted. -- Laura BelinCorrection: The 11 presidential candidates will not appear on the ballotin random order, as was reported in OMRI Special Report No. 1, but inRussian alphabetical order, as follows:1. Vladimir Bryntsalov2. Yurii Vlasov3. Mikhail Gorbachev4. Boris Yeltsin5. Vladimir Zhirinovsky6. Gennadii Zyuganov7. Aleksandr Lebed8. Aman Tuleev9. Svyatoslav Fedorov10. Martin Shakkum11. Grigorii YavlinskiiCANDIDATES AND PARTIESYELTSIN'S CAMPAIGN STRUCTURE. President Yeltsin had considerabledifficulty organizing his campaign staff and finally took personalcontrol on 23 March, according to Obshchaya gazeta of 18-24 April.Yeltsin had initially charged First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg Soskovetswith running the campaign, but his efforts stalled when the Dumaquestioned whether he was using public money to finance Yeltsin's re-election bid. At the same time, Former presidential Chief of StaffSergei Filatov set up the All-Russian Movement of Social Support for thePresident (ODOPP), which consisted of no fewer than 256 organizations,including the 15 initiative committees that collected signatures for thepresident. The confusion, however, was limited to Moscow. In theregions, there are unified campaign staffs that are usually led on paperby the number two person in the republic or region but are actuallycontrolled by the regional executive. Yeltsin now leads what he callsthe "electoral council," though others call it the "headquarters" or the"campaign foundation." His main assistants are Prime Minister ViktorChernomyrdin, who seems to be growing more powerful within Yeltsin'sinner circle, and adviser Viktor Ilyushin, who has taken an extendedleave from his government duties. Current Chief of Staff Nikolai Yegorovis responsible for ties with the regions and local campaign staffs;Federal Security Service Director Mikhail Barsukov is in charge ofguaranteeing order and ties with the "power" ministries; former DeputyPrime Minister Sergei Shakhrai develops campaign tactics; Filatov workswith friendly democratic parties and ensures mass turnout at campaignevents; and Deputy Prime Minister Yurii Yarov takes care of theadministrative details. The "electoral council" does not have its ownstaff, though Filatov's ODOPP has about 100 employees. The staff of thepolitical party Our Home Is Russia is subordinate to Yarov. Former FirstDeputy Prime Minister Anatolii Chubais is supposedly using theconnections he developed as Yeltsin's economic reform coordinator toensure financial support for the campaign. However, Yeltsin has saidthat Chernomyrdin takes care of financial issues and that "everythingwill be fine," suggesting that he is relying mainly on the state budgetfor support. -- Robert OrttungRIGHT-WING PAPER MAKES THE CASE FOR ZYUGANOV. . . The extreme right-wingnewspaper Russkie vedomosti (no. 25) outlined five reasons "Russianpatriots" should support Gennadii Zyuganov for president. First, onlyPresident Yeltsin and Zyuganov have any chance of being elected, sorather than waste their votes, nationalists should back Zyuganov as thelesser of the two evils. Second, Zyuganov's Communist Party of theRussian Federation (KPRF) primarily consists of ethnic Russians, unlikethe Communist Party of the Soviet Union, which the paper claims wasdominated by Jews. Third, the KPRF has the strongest regional network ofall opposition parties. Fourth, Zyuganov and his wife are ethnicRussians (rumors that Boris or Naina Yeltsin have Jewish ancestry arefrequently published in the right-wing press). Finally, Zyuganovunderstands "the Jewish question," and consequently would, if elected,nationalize enterprises bought up in recent years by Jews. Not allRussian nationalists are backing Zyuganov. The writer Eduard Limonov,who is supporting Yurii Vlasov for president, described Zyuganov inSobesednik (no. 13) as a "typical careerist," devoid of talent, and "slyand slippery as only an apparatchik can be sly and slippery." The anti-Semitic, self-described national socialist Aleksandr Barkashov endorsedYeltsin in April, claiming that a Communist return to power would leadto civil war. -- Laura Belin. . .WHILE 10 YOUTH GROUPS DESERT HIM. Ten youth organizations left thecoalition supporting Gennadii Zyuganov for president, Russian mediareported on 5 May. The leader of the poetry club Bronze Age told RussianPublic TV (ORT) that a number of Komsomol members had hit him on thehead with a bottle at a rally after he asked why the word "socialism"did not appear in Zyuganov's election platform. The other nine groupssay they never consciously joined Zyuganov's coalition and thatsignatures on behalf of their organizations were forged. Marat Gelman,leader of an artists' circle, asserted that although Zyuganov claimsthat 191 groups signed an agreement to support his candidacy, 49 of thesignatories are private individuals not representing any realorganization and 14 are leaders of groups "with only one member," NTVreported. -- Laura BelinZHIRINOVSKY DESCRIBES HIS CAMPAIGN STRATEGY. Liberal Democratic Party ofRussia leader Vladimir Zhirinovsky discussed his ability to "cast aspell on the public" in a revealing interview with Argumenty i fakty(no. 18). Zhirinovsky said his sometimes scandalous behavior--forinstance, waving a pair of handcuffs in the State Duma chamber andthreatening to arrest those responsible for breaking up the SovietUnion--would help him take votes away from Communist Party leaderGennadii Zyuganov. "The workers in Bryansk [Oblast] liked the scene withthe handcuffs," he asserted, "and they are [Zyuganov's] electorate."Since "the people want Stalin," he promises to be like Stalin, onlywithout the mass repressions. Zhirinovsky contradicted himself severaltimes during the interview; for instance, he said: "The Chechens mustnot leave Russia. They are good people, although they are a nation ofbrigands." But this too is probably deliberate, since Zhirinovsky revelsin bad press. In fact, he advised "so-called democratic journalists...Ifyou want to destroy me, sing my praises." True to his strategy, in themost recent issue of his party organ Pravda Zhirinovskogo (no. 4), theLDPR leader warned readers that 90% of what the mass media reports is"disinformation." He also credited Stalin with halting the export of rawmaterials from the USSR and helping develop Soviet industry,agriculture, science, and culture. -- Laura BelinANALYSIS AND PREDICTIONSDUDAEV'S DEATH IMPROVES YELTSIN'S CHANCES. The recent death of Chechenseparatist President Dzhokhar Dudaev will improve President Yeltsin'schances for re-election in June, according to Novaya gazeta (no. 15).Before Dudaev's death, the paper contended, it was clear that neither amilitary nor a political settlement of the Chechen conflict could besecured before the presidential election. Moreover, continuing the warwas likely to alienate a considerable number of Yeltsin's supporters,while peace negotiations would displease others. However, Yeltsin'spopularity and electoral prospects would grow if he proposednegotiations that were then rejected by the Chechen side. This scenariois taking place now, the paper suggested, since Dudaev's successor,Zelimkhan Yandarbiev, is refusing to negotiate until an investigation ofthe circumstances of Dudaev's death is carried out. Finally, the paperspeculated, if Yeltsin's team determines late in the game that hischances for re-election are poor, they may stage terrorist acts andattribute them to "Dudaev's avengers," providing a pretext for cancelingor delaying the election. -- Anna ParetskayaVOTERS LAY DOWN CONDITIONS. While 17% of Russian voters unconditionallysupport President Yeltsin for re-election and 36% will never vote forhim, others may vote for him in the upcoming presidential election if hefulfills their demands, Moskovskii komsomolets reported on 6 May. Anopinion poll of 1,600 Russians indicated that the top priority forundecided voters is Yeltsin's ability to pay salaries and pensions ontime; 13% will support him if he meets this condition. (During thecampaign, Yeltsin has promised to solve the problem of wage and pensionarrears, but he has had only limited success.) Concluding a real peaceagreement in Chechnya could add 11% to Yeltsin's support, and returningsavings that people lost due to economic reforms could add another 10%.Five percent of Russians will vote for Yeltsin if other candidates areeven worse (such as Zyuganov or Zhirinovsky). The lowest priority forvoters is success in foreign policy (0.2%). -- Anna ParetskayaCENTRAL, REGIONAL STUDENTS DIFFER IN POLITICAL PREFERENCES. Opinionpolls conducted among Moscow and provincial students show that politicalpreferences of students differ considerably according to their place ofresidence, Obshchaya gazeta (no. 17) reported. The majority of studentsfrom Moscow schools support President Yeltsin since they see him as aguarantor of democratic freedoms, economic and social stability, and animprovement in the social situation. Many students support GrigoriiYavlinskii, and his popularity does not drop as significantly asYeltsin's among students outside Moscow. However, many students doubtYavlinskii's chances of winning and consequently say they will vote forYeltsin. Although Communist leader Gennadii Zyuganov is unpopular amongstudents in the capital, he has many supporters among students fromregional schools. They expect him to change social policy, restore theSoviet Union, and increase Russia's influence in world politics. About6% of students have decided not to participate in the presidentialelection since they believe "life will not change, no matter who comesto power." -- Anna ParetskayaSPECULATION OVER KORZHAKOV'S CALL FOR ELECTION DELAY. Presidentialbodyguard Aleksandr Korzhakov's statement to The Observer and Interfaxthat he wants to postpone the elections has caused widespreadspeculation in the Russian press over his intentions. The liberalKuranty on 7 May claimed that Korzhakov's statements were intended as awarning to those who have adopted a "wait and see" attitude. The paperargued that his comments indicated that if Yeltsin wins, the people whodid not support him will be fired, and that if he loses, the resultswill be annulled and they will be removed anyway. The comments were alsointerpreted as a warning to Zyuganov's supporters not to get their hopesup, because they will not win, whatever the results of the voting.Although it is unclear what will happen if the communists win,Korzhakov's statement, the paper asserted, appears to be intended aspsychological pressure to prevent people from supporting Yeltsin'sopponents. Kommersant-Daily on 7 May argued that the situation shouldnot be overdramatized and that it is entirely possible that Korzhakovwas merely expressing his personal opinion. Korzhakov has in the pastexpressed his distaste for Defense Minister Pavel Grachev. Moskovskiikomsomolets on 7 May argued that Korzhakov's statements reflect a battlewithin Yeltsin's inner circle over whether the election should go aheadthat has grown so intense that it has spilled onto the pages of thepress. The paper claimed that by going public, Korzhakov is trying toexert pressure on the president to accept his position against holdingthe election. Additionally, by making such a statement, Korzhakov mayhave lowered Yeltsin's rating in the polls and therefore driven himcloser to his point of view. -- Robert Orttung=YAVLINSKII ANNOUNCES PROGRAM. Yabloko leader Grigorii Yavlinskii madepublic his campaign program "I choose freedom" on 12 May, laying outplans for the first 730 days of his presidency if he is elected,Nezavisimaya gazeta reported. He plans to stop the Chechen war withinthe first 100 days, and will take measures to halt the implementation ofPresident Yeltsin's plans to rebuild the Chechen economy and organizethe relocation of all who want to leave the republic. Chechnya's statuswill be decided by a referendum. Between November 1996 and April 1997,he plans to increase the minimum wage three times, average governmentsalaries two times, average pensions and stipends two times, and aid forchildren five times. In later months, he would carry out tax, bank, andland reforms, full economic union with the other CIS countries, put ahalt to inflation and increase production. He claimed that prosperitywill only come in 10-15 years, Izvestiya reported on 14 May. -- RobertOrttungZYUGANOV LEADS FIELD IN OFFICIALLY REPORTED FINANCING. Communist leaderGennadii Zyuganov has 1.6 billion rubles ($300,000) in his campaign warchest, ahead of President Yeltsin's 1.4 billion as of 5 May, Segodnyareported 13 May. Zyuganov has spent 773 million, 606 million of whichwas on printed materials. He has not spent any money on the mass mediasince 25 April. Yeltsin provided no spending figures. Candidates arelimited to collecting 19 billion during the course of the campaign. Theofficially published figures do not reflect the candidates' actualspending. Although many of the official reports from the Duma electioncampaign were understated, no charges have been brought forirregularities. -- Robert OrttungCAMPAIGN STARTS IN ELECTRONIC MEDIA. The 11 registered presidentialcandidates may air free and paid political advertisements on radio andtelevision beginning on 14 May. During the next month, each candidatewill receive a total of 30 minutes of free air time on Russian Public TV(ORT), Russian TV (RTR), and St. Petersburg Channel 5. In addition, allcontenders will receive free time on Radio Mayak, Radio Rossii, Radio 1,Radio Yunost, and more than 80 state-run regional radio and televisioncompanies, ITAR-TASS reported on 13 May. The candidates may not buy morethan 30 minutes of paid advertising on ORT, RTR, or St. PetersburgChannel 5, but these limits do not apply to the independent electronicmedia. -- Laura BelinOSCE TO MEDIATE IN CHECHNYA? Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdinhas asked the OSCE to make contacts with the Chechen separatistleadership on behalf of the Russian government commission charged withimplementing President Yeltsin's peace plan, Reuters reported on 13 May,quoting Interfax. Also on 13 May, ITAR-TASS reported that theConfederation of Peoples of the Caucasus had also offered to mediate asettlement. Following the arrest in Moscow on 4 May of Chechen DeputyPrime Minister Beslan Gantemirov on charges of embezzling up to 7million rubles intended for reconstruction in Chechnya, 20 ofGantemirov's associates have been arrested in Grozny on related charges,Russian Public TV (ORT) reported on 13 May. -- Liz FullerST. PETERSBURG MAYORAL CANDIDATES CONSOLIDATE. Three candidates in the19 May St. Petersburg mayoral election have set up a coalition, RussianTV (RTR) reported on 13 May. Former Deputy Mayor Vyacheslav Shcherbakovand local Yabloko leader Igor Artemev withdrew from the race in favor ofVladimir Yakovlev, who for the last three years has been the chairman ofthe city's Economy Committee and Mayor Anatolii Sobchak's first deputy.Another two mayoral candidates, Aleksandr Belyaev and Yurii Boldyrev,may also join the coalition. Last week, the regional branches of severaldemocratic parties refused to back Sobchak and called on his main rivalsto rally behind a single candidate (see OMRI Daily Digest, 10 May 1996).-- Anna ParetskayaEU ENDORSES "ACTION PLAN" FOR RUSSIA. EU foreign ministers agreed to an"action plan" of assistance for Russia on 14 May, Russian and Westernagencies reported. The plan, which EU officials admitted is largely arepackaging of existing programs, is more important as a symbol ofWestern support for President Yeltsin than as a significant shift in EUpolicy. It does, however, call for an intensified EU-Moscow dialogue onEuropean security, an important step given Moscow's continuingopposition to NATO expansion. Meanwhile, in another sign of Westernsupport for Yeltsin, IMF Director-General Michel Camdessus said theelection of Communist candidate Gennadii Zyuganov would disrupt Russianeconomic reform. He implied that the IMF would reconsider its recent$10.2 billion loan to Russia if Zyuganov pursued renationalizationpolicies. -- Scott ParrishSPY SCANDAL ROUNDUP. U.S. Embassy officials told RFE/RL on 13 May thatthey are still trying to determine why U.S. businessman Richard Oppfeltwas expelled from Russia for spying. According to some Russian reports,Oppfelt's expulsion followed his arrest and detention for trying topurchase classified information on Russian naval installations in theFar East. But anonymous Russian diplomatic sources told ITAR-TASS thatOppfelt was never arrested, and had departed Russia voluntarilyfollowing warnings from Russian security officials. Meanwhile, NTVreported on 12 May that the unidentified British agent whose arresttriggered the ongoing espionage row between Moscow and London is a"young, talented, and promising" Russian diplomat, whose motivationswere financial, not ideological. Negotiations seeking a compromiseresolution of the dispute, over which Russia has threatened to expel upto nine British diplomats, continue. -- Scott ParrishEMPLOYMENT SERVICE HEAD SACKED. President Yeltsin issued a decree on 13May dismissing Federal Employment Service head Fedor Prokopev for theinefficient use and misuse of funds intended to create jobs, ITAR-TASSreported. An inspection by the president's Main Control Administrationshowed that on 1 December 1995 the fund had 15.4 billion rubles ($3.3million) on deposit in commercial banks at low interest rates and hadnot recovered 6.4 billion rubles whose term of deposit had run out (fundmoney should be kept in the state bank). In 1995, only 1.96 trillionrubles (34%) of total spending on the service went on "active employmentpolicies," whereas 1.39 trillion (24%) was spent on upkeep, informationservices, and capital investment. Lack of control by central staff, thereport continued, resulted in numerous abuses: money was diverted tobonuses, food allowances, interest-free loans, and real estateinvestment. Cracking down on official abuses is a key plank of Yeltsin'scampaign platform. -- Penny MorvantRUSSIA CALLS FOR UNIFIED CIS ENERGY POLICY . . . Prime Minister ViktorChernomyrdin told a CIS conference on "energy security" in Moscow on 13May that Western companies are trying to win control of the region'senergy reserves and pose a threat to the security of the CIS, NTVreported. He urged the creation of an OPEC-style body for the CIS tocoordinate energy production, export, taxation, and pipelines. Thesestatements do not reflect a change in Russian policy but make explicitwhat has been the de facto policy in recent years--suspicion of Westerninvestment and pressure on CIS partners. Moscow has leverage due to thefact that CIS countries owe it $2.4 billion for natural gas and $600million for other energy deliveries, ITAR-TASS reported on 14 May.Chernomyrdin said that Russia intends to increase the share of gas inits total energy production from the current 44% up to 56% by the year2010, Russian TV (RTR) reported on 13 May. -- Peter Rutland. . . WHILE WESTERN OILMEN LOOK ON. Also on 13 May, Chernomyrdinaddressed the Russian-American oil club, where representatives from 27Russian and U.S. energy companies signed a "memorandum ofunderstanding." Fuel and Energy Minister Yurii Shafranik said that thecompanies involved have signed deals worth $25 billion, but in realityprogress in the Timano-Pechora and Sakhalin off-shore projects isproceeding very slowly. -- Peter RutlandUKRAINIAN BORDER DEMARCATION. Ukraine has demarcated its borders withPoland, Hungary and Slovakia, ITAR-TASS reported on 13 May. Working mapsdelineating the border with Belarus should be complete by the end of theyear. Territorial disputes remain unresolved with Romania. Debatecontinues with Russia on the borders in the Black and Azov seas. Sewageleakage from the Moldovan cities of Soroki and Yampil into Ukrainiangardens and fields is another source of minor border disputes. -- UstinaMarkusRUSSIAN-UKRAINIAN OIL TARIFF DISPUTE CONTINUES. Russian oil supplied toHungary and Slovakia through Ukraine's Druzhba pipeline will increase to1.5 million tons in May from 900,000 tons in April, ITAR-TASS reportedon 13 May. Ukraine has threatened to block the transit of oil for 16Russian oil exporters that refuse to pay an increased transit fee.Ukraine raised the fee at the beginning of this year from $4.53 to $5.2per ton of oil piped through 100 km of Ukrainian territory. Moscow hasinsisted that Russian firms pay the old rate claiming that the pricehike was done unilaterally. -- Ustina MarkusGERMAN DEFENSE MINISTER IN WARSAW. Volker Ruehe in a two-day visit toPoland on 13 May met with Polish President Aleksander Kwasniewski andDefense Minister Stanislaw Dobrzanski to discuss bilateral relations andPoland's efforts to join NATO. Ruehe said Poland will be among the firstnew NATO members, but any specific decisions concerning the expansionwill not be made before 1997. He said that as a defense minister he is"particularly happy about relations between soldiers from bothcountries." In a lecture at the International Relations Center, Ruehesaid it is Germany's duty to facilitate Poland's return to Europe andPoland's role for Germany is "equally important to that of France." --Jakub KarpinskiBROADCAST TELEPHONE CONVERSATION COMPROMISES REPUTATION OF SLOVAKOFFICIALS. Radio Twist, a private Bratislava-based station, on 13 Maybroadcast a recording of a telephone conversation between the head ofthe Slovak Intelligence Service, Ivan Lexa, and Internal AffairsMinister Ludovit Hudek that suggests that the two officials have beentrying to manipulate the results of the investigation into thekidnapping case of Slovak President Michal Kovac's son. President Kovachas long maintained that the kidnapping was organized by Lexa's agencyas an act of political revenge; the government has denied such charges.Radio Twist claims the tape was left in their offices by unknownpersons; however, there is some speculation that the Slovak opposition'scontacts in the secret service obtained the tape. Former Slovak InternalAffairs Minister Ladislav Pittner of the opposition Christian DemocraticMovement is to hold a press conference on 14 May to identify theperpetrators of the kidnapping. -- Jiri PeheSLOVAK HUNGARIANS ASKED TO SIGN DECLARATION OF LOYALTY. Representativesof Slovakia's ruling parties at a meeting in Bratislava on 13 Maydemanded that Hungarian minority leaders adopt a declaration expressingtheir loyalty to the Slovak Constitution and their agreement with theexisting Slovak-Hungarian treaty, Slovak media reported. The governmentparties have made adoption of the declaration a precondition to talks onadopting a law on the use of minority languages and a constitutionalamendment on the rights of ethnic minorities. -- Jiri PeheHUNGARY'S NEW FINANCE MINISTER SUFFERS FIRST PUBLIC DEFEAT. PeterMedgyessy suffered his first public defeat when the government on 10 Maypostponed the planned 1997 reintroduction of interest tax, the BudapestSun reported. Medgyessy was the main advocate of the interest tax, whichwas first introduced in 1988 during his last tenure as finance ministerand was eliminated in 1994. The government is currently seekingalternative budget revenues to compensate for planned cuts in thecurrent 48% personal income tax rate. In other news, Medgyessy has askedformer Finance Minister Mihaly Kupa to be his advisor during the publicintroduction of the state budget reform. -- Zsofia SzilagyiUPDATE ON BULGARIA'S FINANCIAL CRISIS. Bulgaria's currency, the lev, haslost some 70% of its value since the beginning of 1995, plunging thecountry into one of its worst crises since the fall of the communistregime. Premier Zhan Videnov on 10 May urged the parliament to pass lawsthat would shore up the banking system, guarantee deposits, and affectbadly needed privatization measures that the cabinet enacted on 12 May.Videnov announced that unproductive state-owned factories would be shutdown, with workers receiving cash payment compensations. Meanwhile,Bulgarian dailies speculate that the economy is on the brink ofhyperinflation. -- Stan MarkotichThis material was reprinted with permission of the OpenMedia Research Institute, a nonprofit organization with researchoffices in Prague, Czech Republic.For more information on OMRI publications,please write to:  info@omri.cz=ftp://ftp.ifi.uio.no/pub/pgp-----BEGIN PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----Version: 2.2mQCNAjCa/14AAAEEALKTqTI1BVtFs63+rV0zPyTQZ3Mi0iNPrFK0SJw71ypW0QM+medOV8X0UZaeKYg455IdB9QfC7tEi7xWZGPSiGbUxlhuN4hTOonFhIRJg2CDE3iG53OSsh2OHRyM3O0ozTnroKKoFax8Wz9wZQsrNQc5fpbx/JFqG43bm6trFGRjAAURtChOZW16ZXQgPG5lbXpldEBtYWd5YXIuc2lsaWNvbnZhbGxleS5jb20+=WggG-----END PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK-----
