ztsegviselok, akik o mint Keleti kozolte o objektivek ebben a kerdesben. A vizsgalat varhatoan egy-ket nap mulva eredmenyt hoz. A miniszter utasitast adott ki, hogy a vizsgalobizottsag tagjai minden okmanyhoz hozzajuthassanak."Felajanlottam lemondasomat a miniszterelnoknek, hogy szabad keze legyen az ugy kezeleset illetoen" kozolte Keleti Gyorgy. Hozzatette: szerinte masoknak is le kell vonni a megfelelo konzekvenciat ebbol. Horn Gyula miniszterelnok is fogadta az ujsagirokat, hogy kozolhesse, nem fogadja el Keleti lemondasat. Horn ugy fogalmazott, Keleti ertekes tagja a kormanynak, kituno munkat vegez miniszterkent. A kormanyfo intezkedni kivan arrol, hogy tobbet ne fordulhasson elo ilyen hiba. A miniszterelnok szolt arrol is, szeretne, ha minden minisztere hasonlo esetben kovetne Keleti peldajat, akit becsul azert, hogy felajanlotta tavozasat. A miniszterelnok vegul elmondta: varhatoan kedden tajekoztatni tudja az Orszaggyulest az ugy vizsgalatanak eredmenyerol.Ugy tudni, a vizsgalat elozetes megallapitasa szerint feltehetoen a miniszterium egy magas rangu tisztsegviseloje a felelos azert, hogy elmaradt a megfelelo tajekoztatas, illetve nem kertek ki az Orszaggyules engedelyet.=* MEGHIVO * OTODIK NAGY SZITTYA TORTENELMI VILAGKONGRESSZUS (NSZTVK)A ketnapos vilagkongresszus 1996. junius 29-en 10 orakor kezdodik a Zoldmezo Campingben (6764 Balastya, Tanya 374., telefon: 06-60-380-415) Szallast ugyanott merev satrakban biztositanak (agy, matrac, agnemu) Belepes ingyenes, azonban a tetemes koltsegek csokkentesere szivesen veszik a szervezok az adomanyokat -- kulonosen a kulfoldi resztvevoktol.  A tervezett musor es (a felkert eloadok altal visszaigazolt) musor a kovetkezo ( a sorrend valtozhat):1.  Siklosi Andras:     Bevezeto eloadas (Radikalis, forradalmi valtozasok nelkul elsullyed a magyarsag) 2.  Gidai Erzsebet:     Gazdasagi tulelesunk eselyei es az adossag ara 3.  Ducz Laszlo:        A kozottunk elo turulmadar 4.  Raffay Erno:        A trianoni diktatum tarthatatlansaga, reviziojanak jogossaga es szuksegessege 5.  Pesti Jozsef:       A magyarsag eredete es legosibb honfoglalasai 6.  Vodros Attila:      A nemzeti tajekoztatas alattomos ellehetetlenitese a posztkommunizmusban 7.  Kunszabo Ferenc:    A szerves tarsadalom 8.  Kosztin Arpad:      Az erdelyi magyarsag onvedelmi kuzdelmei a nagyroman sovinizmus ellen 9.  Forrai Zoltan:      Arany Hajnal (Osi hitunk ma is latszo nyomai a vilagkulturaban) 10. Agoston Zoltan:     A delvideki magyarsag (el)uldozese es remenyei a megmaradasra a szetesett Jugoszlaviaban 11. Barany Jozsef:      Jezus es a valodi keresztenyseg megtarto ereje a magyar csaladokban es a nemzetben 12. Kiraly B. Izabella: Kikkel es hogyan lehetne osszefogni nemzetunk megmentese erdekeben? 13. Schulek S. Tibor:   Oseink fegyverei, szerszamai, viselete es eletmodja 14. Szalai Robert --     Pongratz Gergely:   1956 igazsaga, dicsosege es uzenete az utokornak 15. Magyar Csaba:       A magyar nepmuveszet jellege es tanulsagai (Magyar Adorjan kutatasai alapjan) 16. Kotyuk Istvan:      A karpataljai magyarsag fuldoklasa az oroszok es ukranok tengereben 17. Praczki Istvan:     A magyar nyelv forrasai es paratlan gazdagsaga 18. Marton Veronika:    Van-e meg jovoje a felvideki magyarsagnak a szlovak kutyaszoritoban? 19. Pap Gabor:          Nimrod, Atilla, Arpad -- fejezetek a magyarok mitikus tortenetebol 20. Pozsonyi Otto:      A Rakoczi Szovetseg, a Hunyadi Janos Szovetseg, a Bocskai Szovetseg es mas szervezetek a magyarsag szolgalataban 21. Kulin Ban --     Vermes Lajos:       A magyarsag es a japan ostortenet osszefuggesei es aktualis kerdesei 22. Kenessey Csaba:     A magyarsag nagy dilemmaja: Kelet vagy Nyugat? 23. Bene Ferenc:        Rovasirasunk a csudak csudaja-A Nagy Szittya Tortenelmi Vilagkongresszus eloadas-sorozatanak idejen -- ugyancsak Siklosi Andras es segitoi szervezeseben -- zajlik (junius 30-an, Opusztaszeren) az Arpad-nap programja, amelyre a kongresszuson resztvevoket is vendegul latjak. Musor: tortenelmi lovasbemutato, vasarnapi szentmise (Barany J. rk. plebanos), Himnusz, versek, unnepi beszedek, a fiatalok eskutetele, koszoruzas, Szekely Himnusz, Szozat, valamint a Feszty-korkep -- fakultativ, tehat tetszes szerinti -- megtekintese. Ara 180 forint/fo.A Vilagkongresszus jelmondata:  "ARPAD SZELLEMEBEN ELORE A BOLDOGABB MAGYAR JOVOERT!"[A Nemzet Szerkesztosege keri mindazon Magyar Honfitarsainkat, akik ebben az evben hazai latogatasra keszulnek, sziveskedjenek figyelembe venni, es jelenletukkel, vagy anyagiakkal tamogatni ezt az otodik eve megrendezesre kerulo, a magyarsag eredetenek tudatositasat, ontudatanak es onerzetenek erositeset szolgalo, magas szinvonalu esemenyt.A jelentkezok -- levelben -- kozvetlenul a foszervezonel jelentkezhetnek (Siklosi Andras, az NSZTVK alelnoke es hazigazdaja, 6723 Szeged, Becsi u. 3.), vagy telefonon/faxon Stolmar G. Ilonanal (tel/fax: 1-412-873-0668, USA. E-mail cim: alistolmar@aol.com) Szallas foglalas ugyanezeken a cimeken lehetseges.]= DEMOKRATA (21) [http://www.siliconvalley.com/demokrata ]Bencsik Andras Nippon itthon Nippon itthon van Magyarorszagon, derul ki heti osszeallitasunkbol, mert a japan reszvetel a millecentenariumi(?) evben meglehetosen gazdag programot iger. Lepjunk tul azon, hogy minek van az iden ezerszaz eves evforduloja, minek nincs, legyunk nagyvonaluak, Arpad bejohetett vegso soron 896-ban is. Inkabb figyeljunk fol arra, hogy a hatalmas Japan megkulonboztetett figyelmet szentel a magyar allamisag ezerszaz eves evfordulojanak.  - Valamint az osztrak millenniumnak is. Mert azon is reszt vesznek. A het szenzacioja persze nem ez, hanem hogy Peto Ivan nagy bajba kerult a minap.  - Tortent pedig, hogy tobbeves nyomozomunkaval Kormos Valeria az utobbi evek legszenzaciosabb oknyomozo riportjat tette kozze a mult heten a Magyar Nemzetben a vicos Fenyo Janos gatlastalan uzleti manovereirol. A riportban megszolal Peto Ivan is, aki, ahogy mondani szokas, elhatarolodik Fenyotol: "ha igazak lennenek azok a pletykak, melyekrol on is hallott, es amelyeket most velem kivan megerosittetni, a Vico szandeka szerint mar regen megszerezte volna a Radio- es Televizioujsagot, privatizalta volna az Athenaeum nyomdat, hogy csak az altalam ismert torekveseit emlitsem." Az SZDSZ elnoke vilagosan leszogezi tovabba: "az SZDSZ elfogadhatatlannak tartja az egyedi protekcionizmust,  ennek kovetkezteben en inkabb olyan panaszokkal talalkozom, hogy az SZDSZ senkinek semmit nem intez el."  - Oszinte szavak, kemeny szavak. Kar, hogy a hiteluk csak egy napig tartott. Mert a masnapi Nepszabadsag teljes kethasabos szerkesztosegi (nevalairas nelkuli) vezercikkben huzta ra a vizes lepedot Fenyore.  - A lepedobol egy csucsoknyi Peto Ivannak is jutott: "Alkerdesek: Kapcsolatnak lehet-e nevezni, ha Peto Ivan, az SZDSZ elnoke hosszas unszolas utan vegul raveszi egyik miniszter ismeroset arra, hogy az tobbszori elharito akcio utan megis fogadja Fenyo Janost?..."  - Nehez lehet most Peto Ivannak. Nincs kinosabb annal, mint amikor az ember hazugsagba keveredik:  emitt dorgo szavakkal ostorozza a korrupciot, amott viszont lebuktatjak mint, hogy is mondjam,... mint  kozbenjarot.  - Most mi lesz? A Nepszabadsag, ahogy mondani szokas, nem egy szelsojobboldali napilap, es megis  alaposan odatett Petonek. Es persze Fenyo Janosnak. Meg Horn Gyulanak, Gal Zoltannak, Csintalan Sandornak.  - Szekeres Imrenek az eredeti riport tett be, mint ahogy a rendkivul plauzibilis Varhelyi Andrasnak is, aki mint kitudodott, ugy fejlodott Antall Jozseftol Torgyan Jozsefig, hogy kozben kepes volt megmaradni a Vico felugyelobizottsaga elnokenek is...  - Bezzeg ideat minalunk nagy a beke es a boldogsag. Egymasra talaltak az ellenzeki partok, s ami ellen  oly hosszan es oly elszantan harcoltak honapokon at, azt most sietve letrehoztak: a Fidesz, az MDF es a KDNP szovetseget, vagyis a Polgari Szovetseget.  - Bizony, nem csalas, nem amitas, a Polgari Szovetseg, hal'istennek, megiscsak osszejott. Igaz, a nagyszeru Szabo Ivan es pompas csapata hianyzik belole. De majd ok is belekerulnek a vege fele, hiszen hova is mennenek mashova.  - Jo ez igy, szep ez igy. Kell az egyseg, kell az egyuve tartozas. Lam, milyen visszatetszo tud lenni odaat, amikor a baloldal egymast marcangolja a koncon.  - Szegeny Szekely Ferencet is meltatlanul uldozi a lelkesen egyesulo ellenzek. Pedig neki tiszta a  lelkiismerete, soha ilyen jo es olcso nem volt a Magyar Televizio. Peldanak okaert a Magyarok cselekedetei cimu nemzetdicsero sorozat is csupan hetszaz- (700) millio forintba kerult. A szamlat a Fodor-Magyar paros allta. Meg mondja valaki, hogy a honszeretet uzlet. Plane, ha az illetot peldaul Koti  Juditnak, Gero Andrasnak vagy Pecsi Veranak hivjak. Utobbi korabban Haraszti Miklos felesege volt.=FREEDOM HOUSE: USA NAGYOVETSEG KONTRA LOVAS ISTVAN - "Lovasnak sok van a rovasan"[Lovas Istvan irasa]Hosszu idon at kell keresgelni a diplomacia evkonyveiben, ameddig olyan durva es suta beavatkozas peldajara bukkanunk, mint amilyenre a  mostani amerikai kovetseg vetemedett egy - vagy, mint latni fogjuk, minden bizonnyal ket - cikkunk megjelenese miatt.De menjunk sorjaban. A Vilaggazdasag c. napilap majus 7-i szamaban tudositott eloszor arrol, hogy foldunk orszagaiban a szabadsag- es polgarjogok alakulasat figyelemmel kisero szervezetek kozul a legismertebb, az amerikai Freedom House, Magyarorszag gazdasagat csak reszben szabadnak minositette. Masnap Lovas Istvan a meg szabad es fuggetlen Uj Magyarorszagban irt vezercikkeben mar arrol is beszamolt, hogy a Freedom House Magyarorszag sajtojat iden is csak reszben minositette szabadnak. Lovas a Freedom House jelenteset reszletezo keziratat az Uj Magyarorszag majus 10-en nyomtatta volna ki, ha 9-en a Kordax-tulajdonos Kelemen Ivan es a kisebbsegi tulajdonosok (Szabo Ivan, Giczy Gyorgy, stb.) reszerol az MDF-es Csoti Gyorgy nem rendez nagytakaritast a szerkesztosegben. A szamitogepbe mar begepelt kezirat igy nem jelenhetett meg.A Freedom House jelentese duhot, elkeseredest es, mint varhato volt, atlatszo "kimagyarazast", valamint az amerikai szervezet elleni tamadasokat valtott ki. Akar Laszlo, a Penzugyminiszterium allamtitkara es Bauer Tamas, a szabaddemokratak gazdasagi szakertoje a Vilaggazdasag majus 9-i szamaban elfogadhatatlannak nevezte, hogy a Freedom House a magyar gazdasagot, szemben a szabadnak minositett cseh es lengyel gazdasaggal, csupan reszben itelte szabadnak. Akar egyebkent kijelentette, hogy az amerikai szervezetet "nem ismeri" es az kulonben sem nemzetkozileg elfogadott minosito szervezet. (A tobb mint fel evszazados multra visszatekinto Freedom House-nak tanacskozasi statusza van az ENSZ Gazdasagi es Tarsadalmi Tanacsanal es reszt vesz az ENSZ Emberi Jogi Bizottsaganak ulesein. A szervezet tiszteletbeli elnoke Max M. Kampelman, az USA volt "emberjogi nagykovete", aki annak idejen a helsinki utokonferenciakon oly emlekezetesen kemenyen targyalt a Szovjetunioval. A Freedom House nehany, nalunk is jol ismert kuratoriumi tagja: Zbigniew Brzezinski volt nemzetbiztonsagi tanacsado, Lane Kirkland, az AFL-CIO, a legnagyobb amerikai szakszervezet vezetoje es Jeane J. Kirkpatrick, az USA volt ENSZ nagykovete.)Majus 13-an az Uj Magyarorszag korkerdesben tudakolta politikusok es szerkesztok - koztunk lapunk - velemenyet abbol az alkalombol, hogy, mint irta az Uj Magyarorszag tevesen cimoldalan, a Freedom House "Magyarorszagot a reszben szabad orszagok kategoriajaba sorolta". (Valojaban a Freedom House Magyarorszagot az altalanos kategoriaban a szabad orszagok koze sorolta.)  Arra a kerdesre, egyetert-e azzal, hogy Magyarorszagon a sajto csak reszben szabad, Acs Gyorgy, a szelsosegesen kormanyparti Magyar Hirlap c. napilap megbizott felelos szerkesztoje kijelentette: "Oszinten szolva, nem is tudom, mennyire hiteles az alaphir, amely szerint odakint nem tekintik szabadnak a magyar sajtot". Acsnak csupan nehany napot kellett varnia, ameddig a kormanyparti Magyar Radio majus 17-i Deli Kronikajaban vegre eloszor  hirt adott arrol, hogy Magyarorszag sajtojat a Freedom House csupan reszben minositette szabadnak. A hiradas - csakugy mint a tovabbi hiradasok - elfelejtette megemliteni, hogy a Boross-kormany idejen a Freedom House  a magyar sajtot szabadnak tekintette es a new yorki szervezet a Horn-era sajtojat mar masodszor tekinti csupan reszben szabadnak.Majus 18-an a napilapok az MTI - fuggetlen hirirodahoz meltatlan kommentarszeru es mentegetodzo - washingtoni tudositasa alapjan irtak a kellemetlen hirrol. Aznap a 16 ora c. radiomusorban Farkas Zoltan keszitett interjut a Richard Merrick-kel, a Freedom House munkatarsaval a minositesrol. Sem az interjut keszito, szelsosegesen SZDSZ-szimpatizans Farkas, sem a musorvezeto, szelsosegesen SZDSZ-szimpatizans Bolgar Gyorgy nem emlitette, hogy a Freedom House a magyar sajtot ezuttal mar masod izben tekinti csupan reszben szabadnak. (Erdemes megemliteni, hogy a Freedom House  megallapitasaival szinte vitazo interjut Bolgarnak az Elet es Irodalom foszerkesztojevel, Kovacs Zoltannal keszitett beszelgetese kovette tobbek kozott Popper Petert,  a miniszterelnok tanacsadojat is erinto mediabotranyrol, amelyben Kovacs a vele vitazo Bolgar ellen kifakadt, amiert Bolgar ketsegbe vonta, hogy a  magyar sajtoban az elhallgatas a modi.)Hetilapunk majus 16-an, tehat a Magyar Radiot egy nappal megelozve kozolte a Freedom House jelentest ugy, ahogyan azt Lovas Istvan az Uj Magyarorszagnak megirta.  (A cikk mellett a Freedom House jovo evi jelenteset varhato arnyalo irasban Bathory Gabor, a Petofi radio keso ejjel, "Ugyeletben" cimmel sugarzott betelefonalos musoranak gazdaja mond bucsut hallgatoinak, ugyanis a Radio vezetoi "azonnal es orokre" letiltottak Bathoryt a mikrofonrol, mert "olyan beszelgeteseknek lehettek...fultanui, ami kellemetlen muzsika volt a mai hatalom birtokosainak.")A szemben levo oldalon hosszabb cikk jelent meg A MUOSZ amerikai dollarral taplalt KGB-s magusai" cimmel. Az alatta elhelyezett karakaturank egy oldalra dolt dagadt disznot abrazolt, U$A felirattal az oldalan. A csocsokon ket szamar lakmarozott, fenekukon MUOSZ es KGB felirattal. Az iras eredetileg egy tavaly szeptemberben indult, orszagos terjesztesu konzervativ amerikai hetilap, a Weekly Standard aprilis 22-i szamaban megjelent cikk csaknem teljes forditasa. Szerzoje Herman J. Obermayer volt napilapszerkeszto es -kiado, aki szamos mediaszeminariumot tartott Magyarorszagon. Obermayer egyebek kozott megirja, hogy az amerikai kovetseg mikent tamogatja dollarszazezrekkel a lebilincselo egyszeruseggel "kommunista szemetnek" (fordito: Lovas Istvan) nevezett MUOSZ-t.Nem sokkal a cikk megjelenese utan a fentebb bemutatott Rick Messick telefonhivast kapott az amerikai kovetseg reszekent mukodo USIS-tol, az amerikai kormany informacios szolgalatatol. Andrea Juhos, a telefonalo amerikai diplomata, Rick Messicket arra kerte, hogy cafolja meg Lovas Istvannak a lapunkban megjelent irasat, amelynek angol nyelvu osszefoglalojat atkuldte. Rick Messick a surgeto hangon eloadott keresen megdobbent, mivel ehhez foghato nyomaskiserlettel meg nem talalkozott. Nem is szolva arrol, hogy ha a cikket megtamadja, sajat szervezetenek, a Freedom House-nak a jelenteset tamadja. No comment - ehhez nem kellene kommentart fuzni, irhatnank. De megis kell. Nemi magyarazatot. Ugyanis  az amerikai kulugyminiszterium nehany honapja megjelent emberjogi jelenteseben a magyar sajtot peldamutatoan szabadnak allitotta be. Marpedig, mint ismeretes, az amerikai kulugyminiszterium jelentesenek legfobb forrasa az amerikai nagykovetseg. Pontosabban, az amerikai sajtoattase, Susan Elbow, es stabja. Oket a Freedom House jelentese a legkinosabban erintette, hiszen az o ertekelesuket vonta ketsegbe. Marpedig az amerikai kulugyminiszterium emberjogi jelenteset nem egyszer erte az a vad, hogy politikai celzattal allitjak ossze. Mint peldaul akkor, amikor az annak idejen "onallo" utakat jaro Ceausescu-fele Romaniarol szolo jelentesben a 2 millios magyar kisebbsegrol szo sem esettSusan Elbow egyebkent Lovas Istvannak regi ismerose. Majus 2-an jelent meg a Demokrata c. hetilapban masodik nyilt levele az amerikai sajtoattasehoz, amelybol kitunik, hogy Elbow asszony - diplomatahoz kevesse illoen - nem hogy keresne az informaciot, de elzarkozik elole. Arra sem volt hajlando, hogy Magyarorszag olyan ot vezeto uzletemberevel talalkozzon, akiket Lovasnak sikerult ravennie arra, kozvetlenul mondjak el Elbow asszonynak, hogy miert nem mernek ellenzeki lapokban hirdetni. A Demokrata - hogy szemleltesse az amerikai nagykovetseg korabbi, elesen kormanyellenes es mostani, a baloldali kormanyt vakon partolo politikaja kozotti kulonbseget - e szamaban keretben jelentette meg az MTV volt kaliforniai ugyvedjenek 1993. szeptembereben keltezett levelet Warren Christopher amerikai kulugyminiszterhez. Leveleben az ugyved arrol panaszkodik, hogy az amerikai kovetseg milyen megengedhetetlen  modon avatkozott be a Nahlik-fele televizio munkajaba es milyen vadakkal illette az akkori MTV vezetoseget. A levelben megnevezett diplomatak: Culpepper, Nealon es Juhos. Az amerikai nagykovetseg vastag dosszieban gyujti anyagat Lovas Istvanrol. A dosszie tartalmanak hitelessegere jellemzo, hogy amikor peldaul 1994-ben Magyarorszagra utazott az Accuracy In Media - Pontossag a Mediaban - nevu konzervativ amerikai szervezet, amely a rendszervaltozast celzo radios elbocsajtasokat helyeselte, a kovetseget is meglatogato amerikaiakat ovtak Lovas Istvantol, mint aki - allitottak -  Csurka Istvan titkos tanacsadoja. A nagykovetseg nem szamitott arra, hogy az amerikaiak, akik kozul nem egy Lovas Istvant mar regebbrol ismerte, ezt az ajandekba kapott informaciot visszamondjak neki. Lovas Istvannak, tartjak az amerikai diplomatak, igen sok van a rovasan. Ket evvel ezelott a MUK neveben allitotta ossze a Freedom House-nak igen reszletes jelenteset a magyarorszagi mediarol. Akkor Kereszty Andras, a MUOSZ vezetoje ezt a jelentest tette felelosse, amiert a Freedom House a magyar sajtotol megvonta a "szabad" besorolast.Iden januarban Lovas Istvan az Uj Magyarorszagban  ket egymast koveto napon egy-egy teljes oldalt elfoglalo terjedelemben jelentette meg a Freedom Househoz irt nyilt levelet a media helyzeterol. [ld.  http://www.siliconvalley.com/nemzet/960101.html  eshttp://www.siliconvalley.com/nemzet/960102.html  - a szerk]Hogy ez mennyiben jarult hozza az idei minositeshez, arrol Kereszty Andras meg nem nyilatkozott. Az amerikai nagykovetseg, az emlitett  Weekly Standard szerint KGB-s gyokeru ujsagiroszervezet egyik bujtatott, fo szponzora es a jelenlegi baloldali kormany merteket veszitett tamogatoja, Rick Messickhez intezett uzenetevel mar nyilatkozott. Arrol legalabbis, hogy idegessege atcsapott a diplomacia teruletetol idegen paranoiaba. = Istvan LOVAS * 2061 Bicske Pf. 99 Hungary ( (+36-22) 350-633 Fax (+36-22) 350-487 Mobile phone (06) 20-423-364 1100263.427@CompuServe.COMMr. Rick Messick Freedom House Washington, DC Fax: 202-296-5101May 20, 1996Dear Mr. Messick:Jonathan Sunley called me and said that you might be interested in an article that I wrote in the May 16, 1996 issue of the weekly Magyar Forum.Incidentally, I happened to be the first in Hungary to break the news that you ranked Hungarys press freedom  as partly free again this year. That was a lead article in the May 8 issue of Uj Magyarorszag, the last opposition daily to go out of business soon.Hungarian Radio reported the findings first at noon on the 17th of May.Sincerely,I. Lovas The following article appeared in the May 16, 1996 issue of the  Hungarian weekly  Magyar Forum on page 11. (Right to the article translated below, Mr. Gabor Bathory, a journalist of the state radio, station Petofi, says good-bye to his listeners  of his late night show. Mr. Bathory, practically the last of the non pro-government radio and television journalists allowed to work, says that management ordered him to stop working with immediate effect and that he was told that he would not be able to work for the rest of his life for allowing certain types of anti-government listeners to call in.)HUNGARY IS PARTLY FREEAccording to a report issued by Freedom House that monitors civil and political rights all over the globe, Hungarys economy and its press are  only partly free.In the opinion of the New York-based organization, there is a bloated bureaucracy in Hungary, and the competent ministry or official is difficult to find. Also, there is no complete freedom in the areas of investments and foreign trade.Regarding freedom of the press, Hungary is also in the category of partl y free countries together with Benin, the Cap Verde Islands, Jordan, Macedonia, Mozambique, Senegal, Ukraine and Slovakia.Freedom House looks separately at the electronic and the print media in examining freedom of the press, and it divides each of them into four sub-groups. B is one of the more interesting sub-groups and it evaluates political pressures and controls of media content. Radio and television fared very badly: Freedom House rewarded the influence of the government on a scale ranging from 0 (best) to 10 (worst) with a score of 8, while the print press it got only a score of 7. In category C - economic influences over media content - was also given a score of 7.Laszlo Akar, under-secretary of the Ministry of Finance, and Tamas Bauer, the economic advisor of the Free Democrats attacked the ranking of Freedom House in the extremely pro-government Vilaggazdasag (World Economy - a daily. Tr.s note) on May 9 under the misleading title Are we also free economically?. According to them, Hungary should have been categorized as free similarly to the Czech Republic and Poland. Mr. Akar has added that he does not know Freedom House. In spite of it, Mr. Akar thinks that Freedom House is for sure not a qualifying organization recognized internationally.Freedom House categorized Hungary as free both during the Antall and the Boross governments. The organization found that, since 1990, Hungarys press was only partly free last year for the first time. This finding led to considerable clashes of opinions and consternation in the pro-government papers. There were opinions that ascribed the ranking of Freedom House to the lay-off of radio employees during the Boross-era. This time, even this justification falls by the wayside since the current government ruled the country throughout 1995 - the period of concern. It is conceivable that Hungarys ranking will further deteriorate next year and it will slide to the worse of the two groups of partly free countries in which there is Romania - improving since last year - and Bulgaria that has poorer results than in the previous year. The fact that the pro-government papers were visibly  upset last year, but, this year, they do not even mention the poor ranking of Hungarys press freedom, shows to what extent the situation has gotten worse. And this also applies to the public service broadcast. However, it is interesting to note that Freedom House categorizes the Czech and the Polish press as free, just as the Czech Republic and Poland. A reminder: these were the two, formerly communist countries in which the system was also changed in the media.Istvan Lovas=REGIONALIS HIREKSLOVAK INFORMATION SERVICE CHIEF ADDRESSES PARLIAMENT. SIS director Ivan Lexa, addressing the parliament on 22 May, strongly attacked President Michal Kovac, the opposition, and various media organizations, Slovak media reported. Lexa denied SIS involvement in the kidnapping of Michal Kovac Jr. last August and rejected the findings of the independent investigative commission headed by Christian Democratic Movement (KDH) deputy Ladislav Pittner. Lexa was repeatedly interrupted by jeers and calls for his resignation, while opposition Democratic Union deputies held up banners calling to an end to "banditry" and the "policy of crime." Democratic Party chairman Jan Langos said Lexa misused his position by delivering a political speech rather than a report, while other opposition deputies noted that Lexa did not even mention how the SIS has used its substantial budgetary allocations. Government coalition deputies expressed full support for Lexa. -- Sharon FisherSLOVAK PARLIAMENT APPROVES FOUNDATION LAW. The parliament on 22 May approved the law on foundations despite the Third Sector Association's ongoing campaign against it, Slovak media reported. Of 154 proposed amendments to the draft law, only 13 were accepted. Members of the ruling Movement for a Democratic Slovakia said the law was needed to stop "foreign subversion," pointing in particular to Hungarian-born U.S. financier, George Soros, who publicly criticized Slovak Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar last year. The law states that foundations must register with the Interior Ministry and have start-up capital of 10,000 crowns ($323), increasing to 100,000 crowns after half a year. Critics fear the law will put an end to many small foundations and threaten the development of a civil society. While the president has the right to veto the law, the parliament can simply pass it again. -- Sharon FisherHUNGARIAN DEFENSE MINISTER OFFERS RESIGNATION. Gyorgy Keleti on 22 May has offered to resign following a dispute over the Hungarian armed forces' decision to send eight MiG-29 aircraft to Poland for military exercises without either his or the parliament's approval. Despite the opposition's sharp criticism of Keleti, Prime Minister Gyula Horn said he would not accept the resignation, Hungarian and Reuters reported. "The defense minister is doing a good job and is a valuable member of the government," Horn stressed. Keleti said an investigative commission headed by Defense Ministry political state secretary Istvan Fodor has been established to determine who authorized the flights. All five opposition parties have insisted on Keleti's resignation, noting that he is politically responsible for the consequences of decisions made by his subordinates. * Sharon FisherYET ANOTHER GENEVA SUMMIT. Faced with numerous and flagrant violations of the civilian provisions of the Dayton accord, the "international community" has decided to summon the presidents of Serbia, Croatia, and Bosnia-Herzegovina to Geneva, Reuters reported on 23 May. The summit, slated for 2 June, will include representatives of the Contact Group countries. The shuttle diplomacy and high-level meetings that the major powers use in the former Yugoslavia have in the past led generally only to paper promises. -- Patrick MooreU.S. WAVERS ON ARRESTING KARADZIC. The "international community" continues to waffle on the fate of indicted war criminal Radovan Karadzic, AFP reported. Since last week negotiators have said they hope he will "disappear from the political scene," adding that they will not insist that he be sent to the war crimes tribunal in The Hague, as the Dayton agreement requires. U.S. State Department Nicholas Burns on 22 May said that "as long as [Karadzic] has been effectively marginalized..., he won't be a candidate in the elections and he won't prevent the elections from occurring." He noted that if this is the case, "I think the elections can go forward and will go forward with him sitting in his bitter isolation in Pale." Bosnian government officials have insisted that Karadzic be ousted and sent to the International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia if the elections are to go ahead. -- Patrick MooreROMANIAN ELECTION UPDATE. Representatives of several opposition parties, meeting on 22 May with President Ion Iliescu, demanded that general and presidential elections be held separately, local media reported. The ballots are scheduled to take place in the fall. The proposal was first advanced by the Liberal Party '93 and is now also backed by the National Peasant Party-Christian Democratic, the National Liberal Party- Democratic Convention, the Hungarian Democratic Federation of Romania, and the Party of Romanian National Unity, which is coalition party of the Party of Social Democracy of Romania (PDSR). Observers believe the proposal stems from the fear that Iliescu's popularity will boost the PDSR's performance at the polls. But the government's position is that the elections should be held at the same time to avoid doubling expenses and to enable the new government to concentrate on economic restructuring. -- Michael ShafirBULGARIAN PRESIDENT SAYS COUNTRY ON VERGE OF COLLAPSE. Zhelyu Zhelev, in an interview with 24 chasa on 22 May, said Bulgaria is on the verge of collapse. He blamed the situation on the ruling Bulgarian Socialist Party, adding that the devaluation of the lev and the ongoing banking crisis may lead to that situation getting out of control. Zhelev commented that the Socialists have failed to work out and implement a mass privatization program and are unfit to govern. Referring to the 1 June primaries for a joint opposition presidential candidate, Zhelev said the motto must be: "from a president of the united opposition to a government of the united opposition." He added that the opposition has a realistic chance of retaining the Presidency, after which it would be able to call early elections and win them. -- Stefan KrauseGRACHEV FORESEES CHECHNYA WITHDRAWAL . . . Russian troops will be withdrawn from Chechnya between 1 June and 1 August, Defense Minister Pavel Grachev told a meeting of military officers in Yekaterinburg on 22 May, ITAR-TASS reported. The same day, a high-ranking military officer told the agency that there were more than 41,000 federal troops in the republic, some 19,000 belonging to the Defense Ministry. Grachev said that after the pullout, only units of the North Caucasus military district would remain in Chechnya. Previously, he had said this would include an army motorized-rifle brigade and a division of Interior Troops. -- Doug Clarke---WHILE TROOPS SUFFER HEAVY LOSSES. At least 22 Russian servicemen were killed and 48 wounded on 22 May while trying to capture the Chechen village of Bamut, ITAR-TASS reported. A report on NTV put the number of Russian dead at 70. For the past year, Chechen separatists have been holed-up in the bunkers and tunnels of a former Soviet nuclear missile silo complex at Bamut. A Defense Ministry spokesman said "only the taking of Bamut can open the way for a Yeltsin visit to Chechnya," ITAR TASS reported. The Chechen prime minister, Nikolai Koshman, claimed that Bamut was the "rebel's last stronghold" and predicted the fighting would be over "within two or three days." -- Doug ClarkeCOMMUNISTS PREDICT YELTSIN WILL STEAL ELECTION. Duma Security Committee Chairman Viktor Ilyukhin, a leading member of the Communist Party (KPRF), predicted on 22 May that "Boris Yeltsin will be appointed for a second term, although Gennadii Zyuganov will win [the election]," ITAR- TASS reported. KPRF Duma deputy and campaign manager Valentin Kuptsov added that he considers Central Electoral Commission Chairman Nikolai Ryabov "Yeltsin's man" and does not trust him to carry out an honest vote count. Meanwhile, accusing Yeltsin of being afraid of a direct dialog, Zyuganov again invited the president to debate him on live television, Russian TV (RTR) reported. -- Laura BelinYELTSIN DECREE BOOSTS KORZHAKOV. President Yeltsin signed a decree on 22 April that gives Presidential Security Service (SBP) head Aleksandr Korzhakov "the rights" of a federal minister, apparently elevating him to cabinet status, according to the text of the decree published in Rossiiskaya gazeta on 21 May. It also designates Korzhakov as "first adviser" to the president, a title previously reserved only for presidential adviser Viktor Ilyushin. The SBP is granted broad powers by the decree, including "insuring the prestige of the president," and the "exposure, prevention, and neutralization" of activity by foreign intelligence services. The conservative Korzhakov's role in the presidential apparatus has often been controversial, most recently when he proposed postponing the upcoming presidential election. -- Scott ParrishYELTSIN FIRES TOP SOCIAL WELFARE OFFICIALS. President Yeltsin fired Yurii Shatyrenko, head of the Social Insurance Fund, and Yevgenii Belyaev, head of State Committee for Sanitary and Epidemiological Inspection, on 22 May, ITAR-TASS reported. Both were accused of mismanagement leading to abuse of funds. Shatyrenko was charged with "gross violations of his duties leading to the financial instability of the fund and rising social tension." An audit of the sanitary service revealed almost one quarter of the allotted funds had been misspent. On 13 May, Yeltsin had fired the head of the Federal Employment Service, Fedor Prokopov, for inefficiency. Also on 22 May, the Duma approved on first reading a long-delayed bill tightening legal penalties for bribe- taking. -- Peter RutlandZHIRINOVSKY BLASTS WEST. Ultranationalist presidential candidate Vladimir Zhirinovsky blamed the West for Russia's decline during two 10- minute free campaign broadcasts aired by Russian Public TV (ORT) on 22 May. U.S. President Bill Clinton, claimed Zhirinovsky, is Russia's "main enemy," adding that Clinton "had accomplished what Hitler couldn't." He listed Russia's "opponents" as the U.S., NATO, Turkey, and China, while urging closer ties with Libya, Iraq, Iran, India, and Eastern Europe. Zhirinovsky slammed plans for NATO expansion, saying NATO troops would soon be near Smolensk, and would "swallow up the territory of Russia." Zhirinovsky also proposed abolishing Russia's ethnic administrative units, claiming that they consume a disproportional share of the federal budget, impoverishing the "Russian" areas of the country. -- Scott ParrishLAW ON TRANSFER OF POWER APPROVED IN SECOND READING. The Duma passed in the second reading a draft law establishing the procedure for transferring power to a newly-elected president, Russian media reported on 22 May. Under the proposed law, the new president would be sworn in on the 30th day after election results are officially released, at which time the government serving under the outgoing president would have to resign. During the month before taking office, the president-elect would be allowed to attend meetings of the Security Council and other federal agencies. According to Communist Duma deputy Oleg Mironov of the Legislation Committee, the Duma made nearly all the changes recommended by President Yeltsin when the law was first proposed, RTR reported. On the same day, the Duma again failed to override the Federation Council's veto of the law on election monitoring (see OMRI Daily Digest, 20 May 1996), NTV reported. -- Laura BelinDEPUTY JUSTICE MINISTER SHOT DEAD. Deputy Justice Minister Anatolii Stepanov was killed at his home in Moscow by a gun shot to the head on the morning of 23 May, ITAR-TASS reported. Stepanov's responsibilities included supervision of the work of attorneys and notaries. -- Peter RutlandRUSSIA DENIES SELLING MISSILE TECHNOLOGY TO CHINA. Russian diplomats dismissed concerns expressed by U.S. Secretary of Defense William Perry that China is attempting to purchase SS-18 missile technology from Russia, ITAR-TASS reported on 22 March (see OMRI Daily Digest, 22 May 1993). The agency cited anonymous "high-ranking" diplomats as saying that Perry's statement "appears incorrect," although they added that Russia is studying the U.S. claims. The diplomats said that since Perry had not specified exactly what type of technology China was interested in, and had suggested that "non-governmental" organizations in Russia might be involved in unauthorized export activities, it would take time to fully investigate the charges. -- Scott ParrishThis material was reprinted with permission of the Open Media   Research Institute, a nonprofit organization with research offices in   Prague, Czech Republic. For more information on OMRI publications,   please write to:  info@omri.cz
